Length:
Habitus 800 µm; sum of all somites 935 µm; cephalothorax 255 µm; genital double-somite 130 µm. Habitus fusiform (
Fig. 11A
). Colour of preserved specimen yellowish brown. Surface of cuticle densely covered with small pores. Cephalothorax gradually attenuating anteriorly. Rostrum broadly rounded and partially fused at base with cephalothorax, with two small sensilla subapically. Genital double-somite with short transverse chitinous stripe ventrally (
Fig. 11B
). Penultimate somite with rounded pseudoperculum (
Fig. 11C
).
